Skip the common_ops_sm90_build target in sgl-kernel for DGX Spark GB10.

Problem:
  sgl-kernel's CMakeLists.txt declares TWO parallel targets that build the
  same SOURCES list into the same `common_ops` module, just with slightly
  different compile flags and install destinations:

    common_ops_sm90_build   -> sgl_kernel/sm90/common_ops.*.so
                              (compiled with -use_fast_math)
    common_ops_sm100_build  -> sgl_kernel/sm100/common_ops.*.so
                              (compiled without -use_fast_math, "precise math")

  At runtime, sgl-kernel/python/sgl_kernel/load_utils.py's
  _load_architecture_specific_ops() picks ONE of them based on
  torch.cuda.get_device_capability():

      if compute_capability == 90:
          ops_subdir = "sm90"
      elif compute_capability is not None:
          ops_subdir = "sm100"   # <-- GB10 (121) lands here

  GB10 has compute capability 12.1. It unconditionally loads the sm100
  variant; the sm90 directory is never opened. The sm90 variant is
  therefore dead code on this fleet — every TU in SOURCES is compiled
  twice (once for each target), and only the sm100 copy is ever used.

  On top of that, the sm90 target gets the same sgl-kernel arch list
  that sgl-kernel-arch-prune.patch strips down (sm_121a only), so the
  generated SASS is IDENTICAL to the sm100 target except for the
  -use_fast_math nuance. The entire sm90 compile is pure waste.

Fix:
  Wrap all four scattered references to common_ops_sm90_build in
  `if (FALSE) ... endif()` blocks:

    1. The Python_add_library + target_compile_options +
       target_include_directories + set_target_properties block
    2. The target_link_libraries() call
    3. The target_compile_definitions() call with
       FLASHATTENTION_DISABLE_* defines
    4. The install(TARGETS ...) call

  Using if(FALSE) instead of outright deletion preserves the upstream
  structure so future CMake drift is visible in plain diffs; semantically
  it's equivalent to removing the target entirely.

Runtime safety:
  On GB10 nothing changes — load_utils already never looks in sgl_kernel/sm90.
  The sm90 subdirectory is simply absent from the resulting wheel.

  This patch is UNSAFE to apply on a build that will run on a Hopper GPU
  (compute_capability == 90). Those need the sm90 variant, and this patch
  removes it. This is acceptable here because the entire dgxarley fleet
  is DGX Spark GB10; no Hopper silicon is in scope. Do not deploy the
  resulting wheel to H100/H200.

Expected impact:
  - Cuts the remaining core sgl-kernel compile time roughly in half:
    every SOURCES entry compiled once instead of twice.
  - Wheel shrinks by the size of sgl_kernel/sm90/common_ops.*.so (which,
    with arch-prune, is already smaller than upstream but still a
    sizeable duplicate).
  - Orthogonal to arch-prune and disable-fa3: this patch stacks cleanly
    on top of both (patch auto-offsets the four hunks).

Apply to: sgl-kernel/CMakeLists.txt, inside the Dockerfile builder stage,
BEFORE the sgl-kernel `uv build --wheel` step.

Upstream source: sgl-project/sglang tag v0.5.10

--- a/sgl-kernel/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/sgl-kernel/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -338,6 +338,14 @@
 
 # =========================== Common SM90 Build ============================= #
 # Build SM90 library with fast math optimization (same namespace, different directory)
+# dgxarley sgl-kernel-skip-sm90-target.patch: the common_ops_sm90_build target
+# produces sgl_kernel/sm90/common_ops.*.so, which is ONLY loaded by sgl-kernel's
+# load_utils._load_architecture_specific_ops() when compute_capability == 90
+# (Hopper H100). On DGX Spark GB10 (compute_capability 121) the runtime always
+# loads sgl_kernel/sm100/common_ops.*.so instead, so this whole target compiles
+# dead code. Wrapped in if(FALSE) to preserve upstream structure for future
+# drift diffing while skipping the compile entirely.
+if (FALSE)
 Python_add_library(common_ops_sm90_build MODULE USE_SABI ${SKBUILD_SABI_VERSION} WITH_SOABI ${SOURCES})
 
 target_compile_options(common_ops_sm90_build PRIVATE
@@ -349,6 +357,7 @@
     OUTPUT_NAME "common_ops"
     LIBRARY_OUTPUT_DIRECTORY "${CMAKE_CURRENT_BINARY_DIR}/sm90"
 )
+endif()
 
 # =========================== Common SM100+ Build ============================= #
 # Build SM100+ library with precise math (same namespace, different directory)
@@ -389,15 +398,21 @@
     ${CMAKE_CURRENT_BINARY_DIR}/mscclpp-build
 )
 
+# dgxarley sgl-kernel-skip-sm90-target.patch: target deleted above, ref skipped
+if (FALSE)
 target_link_libraries(common_ops_sm90_build PRIVATE ${TORCH_LIBRARIES} c10 cuda cublas cublasLt mscclpp_static)
+endif()
 target_link_libraries(common_ops_sm100_build PRIVATE ${TORCH_LIBRARIES} c10 cuda cublas cublasLt mscclpp_static)
 
 # sparse flash attention
+# dgxarley sgl-kernel-skip-sm90-target.patch: target deleted above, ref skipped
+if (FALSE)
 target_compile_definitions(common_ops_sm90_build PRIVATE
     FLASHATTENTION_DISABLE_BACKWARD
     FLASHATTENTION_DISABLE_DROPOUT
     FLASHATTENTION_DISABLE_UNEVEN_K
 )
+endif()
 target_compile_definitions(common_ops_sm100_build PRIVATE
     FLASHATTENTION_DISABLE_BACKWARD
     FLASHATTENTION_DISABLE_DROPOUT
@@ -407,7 +422,10 @@
 # Install to different subdirectories
 # CMake will find the built libraries in their respective LIBRARY_OUTPUT_DIRECTORY locations
 # and install them to the specified destinations
+# dgxarley sgl-kernel-skip-sm90-target.patch: target deleted above, install skipped
+if (FALSE)
 install(TARGETS common_ops_sm90_build LIBRARY DESTINATION sgl_kernel/sm90)
+endif()
 install(TARGETS common_ops_sm100_build LIBRARY DESTINATION sgl_kernel/sm100)
 
 # ============================ Optional Install: FA3 ============================= #
